# FS25_FieldToDoList - Project Rules

## Release and Build

- Keep `modDesc.xml` version unchanged unless the user explicitly requests a release bump.
- Preferred local build command: `python3 tools/generate_assets.py && ./build.sh`.
- After mod updates, do a full FS25 restart.

## Save and Runtime Safety

- Access savegame `fields.xml` only via `FieldSavegameReader` (no ad-hoc direct file reads in other modules).
- Current project state uses guarded disk reads (`FieldSavegameReader.ENABLE_DISK_READ = true`) with cache and save/load protections.
- Avoid repeated/looped file reads in menu/update paths; prefer cached values.
- Avoid SCS field-map loops in menu/update paths (`buildFieldMap`/`enumerateFields`).
- Keep deferred startup reads (`deferReadsUntilGameplay`) to avoid load deadlocks.

## UI and To-Do Behavior

- To-do ordering is based on `sortIndex` (user order), not work-order presets.
- Keep moved task selected after Up/Down; clear selection after delete.
- Guard SmoothList reload selection (`ignoreTaskSelectionChanged`) and sync by task id, not row index.
- Keep mini button labels `Hoch` / `Runter`; no drag-and-drop.

## HUD and Logging

- HUD shows manual tasks only (`getManualTasksForDisplay()`), max 5 open tasks.
- Keep HUD simple (plain panel, no settings line in HUD).
- In `InGameMenuIntegration`, use `Logging.info`/`Logging.warning`; avoid `print()`.

## Task and Advisor Rules

- Open tasks render above completed tasks.
- Completed tasks capped at 10; newest completed goes to top of completed group.
- `moveTask` must not cross open/completed boundaries.
- While `isWithered`, keep plow and roller incomplete in auto-complete checks.
- For organic mode display, use `getWorkOrderDisplayLabel()` (not preset label).

## Known Open Bug (Next Session)

- Field 14 can still be misclassified as grass after plowing.
- Priority fix area: `FieldAdvisor.isGrassFieldState` and `getEnrichedFieldState` so live `PLOWED` wins over stale grass metadata.
